  "prompt": "Without NOC in present state, can I pay lifetime road tax in new state for my two wheeler?",
  "response": "Generally, without a No Objection Certificate (NOC) from the original state of registration, it can be challenging to pay lifetime road tax in a new state for your two-wheeler. Here's what you typically need to do:\n\n1. Obtain NOC from original state\n- Get NOC from the Regional Transport Office (RTO) where vehicle was initially registered\n- Pay pending taxes/penalties\n- Submit necessary documents\n\n2. Alternative procedure (if NOC is difficult)\n- Pay transfer fees\n- Submit proof of ownership\n- Clear all previous dues\n- Get vehicle fitness certificate\n- Pay road tax in new state\n\n3. Required documents usually include\n- Registration certificate\n- Insurance certificate\n- Pollution under control (PUC) certificate\n- Address proof\n- Identity proof\n- Original invoice/sale deed\n\n4. Specific procedures vary by state\n- Each state has slightly different regulations\n- Recommend checking with local RTO\n\n5. Potential challenges without NOC\n- May face legal complications\n- Possible penalties\n- Risk of vehicle being impounded\n\nBest advice: Obtain NOC from original state before attempting to pay lifetime road tax in new state.",
